# Over and Under

## Introduction @showdialog

Now that you have a peach that moves, let's add the ability to jump hurdles.

![Make your peach jump dangerous pits of hurdle](/static/skillmap/peachtree/intro_peach_race.gif "Animated peach with black sunglasses on track with hurdles on the ground and branches above")




## 2. Remember

Take a look at the code that's already in your workspace.

You should see the blocks that add gravity, make your peach start moving,
and set the camera to follow you along the track.




## 3. Make the Jump

You'll notice some hurdles on the track.

Help your peach avoid them when you press the (A) button.

---


- :game: From ``||controller:Controller||``, drag the <br/>
``||controller:on [A] button [pressed]||`` <br/>
container into an empty area of the workspace.

- :paper plane: Inside of the <br/>
``||controller:on [A] button [pressed]||`` <br/>
container, add a new <br/>
``||sprites:set [mySprite] [x] to [0]||`` block.

- :mouse pointer: Change ``||sprites:[x]||`` to ``||sprites:[vy (velocity y)]||`` <br/>
so you can make the peach move in the up/down direction.

- :mouse pointer: Change **0** to **-200** to send the peach upward with each press of the (A) button.

```blocks
let mySprite: Sprite = null

controller.A.onEvent(ControllerButtonEvent.Pressed, function () {
    mySprite.vy = -200
})
```



## 4. Play it Again

Remember to play your game again each time you make a change.

Can you see the effects of the code you just wrote?




## 5. Hurdles


Now that you can jump the hurdles, let's make them dangerous.

---

- :tree: From ``||scene:Scene||``, drag the <br/>
``||scene:on [sprite] of kind [Player] overlaps [ ] at [location]||`` <br/>
container into an empty area of the workspace.

- :paint brush: Click the checkerboard image and change it to the **hurdle** tile.<br/>
![Make your peach jump dangerous hurdles](/static/skillmap/peachtree/hurdle.png "track hurdle")

- :circle: From ``||game:Game||``, snap a <br/>
``||game:game over <LOSE>||`` <br/>
block into the new container.


```blocks
scene.onOverlapTile(SpriteKind.Player, assets.tile`hurdle`, function (sprite, location) {
    game.over(false)
})
```



## 6. Branches

Pressing the (A) button more than once might send you into a tree branch.
Let's make the branches dangerous, too.


---

- :mouse pointer:  Follow the same steps to end the game when your sprite overlaps the
**branches** as you did for the **hurdle** tile. <br/>
![Avoid the spikes!](/static/skillmap/peachtree/branches.png "branches hanging")

_üí° Need a little help figuring out what this step should look like? Click the lightbulb button below for a peek at the blocks we recommend._


```blocks
scene.onOverlapTile(SpriteKind.Player, assets.tile`branches`, function (sprite, location) {
    game.over(false)
})
```



## 7. Take a Look!

Click back to the game window to see how everything is coming together.

---

You should be able to jump the hurdles by pressing the (A) button and the game
should end when you hit the hurdle or a branch.



## 8. End of the Track

We have a way to lose, now we need a way to win.

At the end of the track, there is a set of flag tiles.

---

- :mouse pointer:  Follow the same steps to end the game when your sprite overlaps
a **finish** tile as you did for the **hurdle** tile.
<br/>
![Get to the cave](/static/skillmap/peachtree/finish.png "Red finish banner with yellow letters ‚ÄúFI‚Äù")


- :mouse pointer: Finish by changing the ``||game: game over <LOSE>||`` to say ``||game: game over <WIN>||``.


```blocks
scene.onOverlapTile(SpriteKind.Player, assets.tile`finish2`, function (sprite, location) {
    game.over(true)
})
```


## Finale

Congratulations!

You've created your own running game!

Race to the end of the track and once you're finished playing,
click **Done** to head back out to the skillmap where you can
play the next level and add customizations to your game.


```template

let mySprite = sprites.create(assets.image`peach`, SpriteKind.Player)
mySprite.ay = 500
mySprite.vx = 100
scene.cameraFollowSprite(mySprite)
```



```customts
tiles.setTilemap(tilemap`level1`)
scene.setBackgroundImage(assets.image`background`)
```
